translate ru strings:

    old "One week had passed since they had first set foot beyond the road."
    new "One week had passed since they had first set foot beyond the road."

    old "A week since they had broken their own wagons and transformed them."
    new "A week since they had broken their own wagons and transformed them."

    old "Upon the back of each man and woman now balanced a weight as great as they could manage."
    new "Upon the back of each man and woman now balanced a weight as great as they could manage."

    old "The great wagons, now converted to sleds that could be pulled across the desert sand, were dragged along by great ropes."
    new "The great wagons, now converted to sleds that could be pulled across the desert sand, were dragged along by great ropes."

    old "Soldiers were rotated in and out from pulling the great ropes."
    new "Soldiers were rotated in and out from pulling the great ropes."

    old "The desert, ever treacherous, continued to drag the soldiers deeper."
    new "The desert, ever treacherous, continued to drag the soldiers deeper."

    old "Their feet sank deep into the sand, slowing down their already reduced march to a crawl."
    new "Their feet sank deep into the sand, slowing down their already reduced march to a crawl."

    old "And above all, there was the merciless assault of the sun."
    new "And above all, there was the merciless assault of the sun."

    old "Where first the soldiers had cried out against it, hurled their insults, there was now only a brooding hatred for the thing."
    new "Where first the soldiers had cried out against it, hurled their insults, there was now only a brooding hatred for the thing."

    old "Those who dared to say anything of the sun, the heat, were met only by angry glares."
    new "Those who dared to say anything of the sun, the heat, were met only by angry glares."

    old "Each knew of the torment of the sun. Each knew of the torment of the heat. None needed the torment of a fool speaking the obvious."
    new "Each knew of the torment of the sun. Each knew of the torment of the heat. None needed the torment of a fool speaking the obvious."

    old "And so, with each passing day, they ventured further and deeper into the desert."
    new "And so, with each passing day, they ventured further and deeper into the desert."

    old "Guided by the measures of the shadows, the rising and setting of the sun, they did their best to keep their course."
    new "Guided by the measures of the shadows, the rising and setting of the sun, they did their best to keep their course."

    old "After another hard day's march, the company set up camp and Sarah took what little rest she could find."
    new "After another hard day's march, the company set up camp and Sarah took what little rest she could find."

    old "Leaning back against a rock, a rare bit of hard surface, she let the embers of the campfire glow on her face."
    new "Leaning back against a rock, a rare bit of hard surface, she let the embers of the campfire glow on her face."

    old "Samayra sat next to her."
    new "Samayra sat next to her."

    old "The poor girl had been born to a life in the palace and now she had to suffer through something even Sarah struggled with."
    new "The poor girl had been born to a life in the palace and now she had to suffer through something even Sarah struggled with."

    old "Sarah could see in her face that she tried to be strong, but the trip was taking a toll on her frail body."
    new "Sarah could see in her face that she tried to be strong, but the trip was taking a toll on her frail body."

    old "Before, Samayra had been able to ride in the wagons, but now she had to march most days, same as the rest."
    new "Before, Samayra had been able to ride in the wagons, but now she had to march most days, same as the rest."

    old "Sarah had tried to make an exception for the girl, but there was simply no space left anywhere."
    new "Sarah had tried to make an exception for the girl, but there was simply no space left anywhere."

    old "Hey..."
    new "Hey..."

    old "Her voice was soft, her eyes hollow and distant."
    new "Her voice was soft, her eyes hollow and distant."

    old "She trembled and shivered in the cold desert night."
    new "She trembled and shivered in the cold desert night."

    old "How are you holding up?"
    new "How are you holding up?"

    old "Sarah almost instantly felt stupid for asking the girl. Of course she'd lie."
    new "Sarah almost instantly felt stupid for asking the girl. Of course she'd lie."

    old "I'm...ok, I just need to catch up a bit."
    new "I'm...ok, I just need to catch up a bit."

    old "Suddenly, her back arched and she began to cough."
    new "Suddenly, her back arched and she began to cough."

    old "Sarah could hear a deep rattle in the poor girl's lungs."
    new "Sarah could hear a deep rattle in the poor girl's lungs."

    old "Sarah opened her arms."
    new "Sarah opened her arms."

    old "Eagerly, Samayra leaned closer, falling into Sarah's embrace."
    new "Eagerly, Samayra leaned closer, falling into Sarah's embrace."

    old "The heat. The cold. The heat again. It was taking a toll on even the strong, and Samayra's body was not that."
    new "The heat. The cold. The heat again. It was taking a toll on even the strong, and Samayra's body was not that."

    old "Just stay here with me, close to the fire."
    new "Just stay here with me, close to the fire."

    old "She felt Samayra nodding against her."
    new "She felt Samayra nodding against her."

    old "Just for a moment..."
    new "Just for a moment..."

    old "Sarah stroked the girl's hair."
    new "Sarah stroked the girl's hair."

    old "Yes, just for a moment."
    new "Yes, just for a moment."

    old "Together, they sat near the campfire, gathering what little warmth they could manage in this desert night."
    new "Together, they sat near the campfire, gathering what little warmth they could manage in this desert night."

    old "Staring into the fire, and feeling the poor girl's lithe frame against her own, she felt memories from long ago return to her."
    new "Staring into the fire, and feeling the poor girl's lithe frame against her own, she felt memories from long ago return to her."

    old "Her brother, oddly enough."
    new "Her brother, oddly enough."

    old "More than once she'd cradled him, just as she now held Samayra."
    new "More than once she'd cradled him, just as she now held Samayra."

    old "Sarah had related to Samayra, a princess like herself, cast out into a cruel world, but perhaps there was also an element of her brother in the girl."
    new "Sarah had related to Samayra, a princess like herself, cast out into a cruel world, but perhaps there was also an element of her brother in the girl."

    old "A soft soul, perhaps unfite by nature for what the world demanded of her."
    new "A soft soul, perhaps unfite by nature for what the world demanded of her."

    old "It was always the kind ones that suffered the most, Sarah thought."
    new "It was always the kind ones that suffered the most, Sarah thought."

    old "Do you think I'm going to survive?"
    new "Do you think I'm going to survive?"

    old "Sarah felt her heart skip a beat as the soft words of Samayra reached her."
    new "Sarah felt her heart skip a beat as the soft words of Samayra reached her."

    old "Sarah lied."
    new "Sarah lied."

    old "You're going to make it through, I'm sure of it."
    new "You're going to make it through, I'm sure of it."

    old "Again the girl's cough revealed just how weak she really was."
    new "Again the girl's cough revealed just how weak she really was."

    old "Sarah wanted her to live. But out here, what could she do? Each day she could see Samayra grow weaker."
    new "Sarah wanted her to live. But out here, what could she do? Each day she could see Samayra grow weaker."

    old "I'm going to find you a place to ride on one of the sleds, alright?"
    new "I'm going to find you a place to ride on one of the sleds, alright?"

    old "She felt Samayra shake her head."
    new "She felt Samayra shake her head."

    old "No, I want to...I want to walk...just like the others..."
    new "No, I want to...I want to walk...just like the others..."

    old "I'm a commander; your commander. I'm ordering you to ride on one of the sleds."
    new "I'm a commander; your commander. I'm ordering you to ride on one of the sleds."

    old "Sarah didn't hear another objection, though perhaps it was simply because the girl didn't have it in her to fight back."
    new "Sarah didn't hear another objection, though perhaps it was simply because the girl didn't have it in her to fight back."

    old "Sarah tried to search her mind for a solution."
    new "Sarah tried to search her mind for a solution."

    old "The only spaces left were the sleds used as makeshift hospice wards."
    new "The only spaces left were the sleds used as makeshift hospice wards."

    old "There the wounded, exhausted and sick were dragged along, but they offered little hope."
    new "There the wounded, exhausted and sick were dragged along, but they offered little hope."

    old "Most refused to be put on them, knowing that they meant death."
    new "Most refused to be put on them, knowing that they meant death."

    old "She had heard the wailing of those confided to the medical sleds. Thinking of putting Samayra among them, made her fearful."
    new "She had heard the wailing of those confided to the medical sleds. Thinking of putting Samayra among them, made her fearful."

    old "Exhaustion alone was a great danger for the girl, but a simple infection might mean the end."
    new "Exhaustion alone was a great danger for the girl, but a simple infection might mean the end."

    old "Then again, her body was too frail to continue the march..."
    new "Then again, her body was too frail to continue the march..."

    old "Sarah felt a tear run past her face, unsure of what to do."
    new "Sarah felt a tear run past her face, unsure of what to do."

    old "If I die..."
    new "If I die..."

    old "Sarah hushed her again."
    new "Sarah hushed her again."

    old "Don't talk like that. You're going to be alright."
    new "Don't talk like that. You're going to be alright."

    old "Sarah tried to keep the emotion from her voice."
    new "Sarah tried to keep the emotion from her voice."

    old "...at least I'll have seen the world."
    new "...at least I'll have seen the world."

    old "Sarah continued to stroke the girl's hair."
    new "Sarah continued to stroke the girl's hair."

    old "What a cruelty if this was all she'd ever get to see of the world."
    new "What a cruelty if this was all she'd ever get to see of the world."

    old "No, you'll get to see so much more."
    new "No, you'll get to see so much more."

    old "Remember the snow? We can go to Rossana, and I'll show you what it looks like."
    new "Remember the snow? We can go to Rossana, and I'll show you what it looks like."

    old "She heard the girl softly laugh."
    new "She heard the girl softly laugh."

    old "The snow...the whole world covered in white...you're a liar..."
    new "The snow...the whole world covered in white...you're a liar..."

    old "Sarah hugged the girl, trying to pass her body heat to her."
    new "Sarah hugged the girl, trying to pass her body heat to her."

    old "You'll see, I promise."
    new "You'll see, I promise."

    old "Sarah could feel Samayra's body rise and fall, slower and slower."
    new "Sarah could feel Samayra's body rise and fall, slower and slower."

    old "Then, finally, she could hear the soft snoring of the girl, now lost to sleep."
    new "Then, finally, she could hear the soft snoring of the girl, now lost to sleep."

    old "Sarah smiled, knowing the girl would last a bit longer."
    new "Sarah smiled, knowing the girl would last a bit longer."

    old "Softly, she lifted her from her arms and placed her down near the campfire, placing a blanket on her and pulling it up close to her neck."
    new "Softly, she lifted her from her arms and placed her down near the campfire, placing a blanket on her and pulling it up close to her neck."

    old "For a brief moment, Sarah held the girl's image in her mind."
    new "For a brief moment, Sarah held the girl's image in her mind."

    old "It felt so ethereal, even now. Like the winds could pick up and simply blow her away."
    new "It felt so ethereal, even now. Like the winds could pick up and simply blow her away."

    old "She was a creature so delicate, much like Sarah's brother, that one could not help but feel a primal desire to protect."
    new "She was a creature so delicate, much like Sarah's brother, that one could not help but feel a primal desire to protect."

    old "But Sarah could only protect her from enemies she could swing a sword at."
    new "But Sarah could only protect her from enemies she could swing a sword at."

    old "Whatever was hacking away at the girl's lungs, racking her body, was beyond her ability to combat."
    new "Whatever was hacking away at the girl's lungs, racking her body, was beyond her ability to combat."

    old "Sarah stood up and began to walk away, content to leave the girl by the warmth of the fire. She would make it through the night, that much she knew."
    new "Sarah stood up and began to walk away, content to leave the girl by the warmth of the fire. She would make it through the night, that much she knew."

    old "Whatever came next..."
    new "Whatever came next..."

    old "Having said still for long enough, eager to get some movement, Sarah stood up and began to walk away."
    new "Having said still for long enough, eager to get some movement, Sarah stood up and began to walk away."

    old "Walking through the camp was like a labyrinth."
    new "Walking through the camp was like a labyrinth."

    old "Everywhere, small groups of soldiers sat around campfires, gathered for warmth and companionship."
    new "Everywhere, small groups of soldiers sat around campfires, gathered for warmth and companionship."

    old "Walking in between the groups, just outside the darkness, one could be alone yet surrounded."
    new "Walking in between the groups, just outside the darkness, one could be alone yet surrounded."

    old "Everywhere she looked, Sarah could see something had begun to change."
    new "Everywhere she looked, Sarah could see something had begun to change."

    old "Where once the fires had been places of celebration, where the soldiers sang and drank until the next day, they were now something very different."
    new "Where once the fires had been places of celebration, where the soldiers sang and drank until the next day, they were now something very different."

    old "Now they were pits of shared misery, where each sat and lingered in silence, content only to share their grudges."
    new "Now they were pits of shared misery, where each sat and lingered in silence, content only to share their grudges."

    old "Saying nothing, she could see that their eyes spoke volumes. Deep, dark and hollow. Their angry souls peered out through their eyes."
    new "Saying nothing, she could see that their eyes spoke volumes. Deep, dark and hollow. Their angry souls peered out through their eyes."

    old "Sarah worried about what was coming over the camp."
    new "Sarah worried about what was coming over the camp."

    old "Suddenly, a shade approached her."
    new "Suddenly, a shade approached her."

    old "Lonely?"
    new "Lonely?"

    old "Sarah smiled at Kate in the dark."
    new "Sarah smiled at Kate in the dark."

    old "I have an abundance of friends, don't you know?"
    new "I have an abundance of friends, don't you know?"

    old "Pretty sure I'm the only friend you have."
    new "Pretty sure I'm the only friend you have."

    old "Kate gestured towards where Sarah had come from."
    new "Kate gestured towards where Sarah had come from."

    old "How is the girl?"
    new "How is the girl?"

    old "She pretends to be stronger than she is. I worry about her."
    new "She pretends to be stronger than she is. I worry about her."

    old "She has developped a nasty cough..."
    new "She has developped a nasty cough..."

    old "Yeah, she isn't the first. It's been going around the camp. Still though, given how small she is..."
    new "Yeah, she isn't the first. It's been going around the camp. Still though, given how small she is..."

    old "Yeah...I don't know."
    new "Yeah...I don't know."

    old "Kate placed her hand on Sarah's shoulder."
    new "Kate placed her hand on Sarah's shoulder."

    old "She's stronger than you think, she might surprise you."
    new "She's stronger than you think, she might surprise you."

    old "Thank you, I needed to hear some kind words."
    new "Thank you, I needed to hear some kind words."

    old "Now, tell me, where were you headed right about now?"
    new "Now, tell me, where were you headed right about now?"

    old "Just wandering really."
    new "Just wandering really."

    old "Thought about drinking myself into a stupor, but I haven't the energy for it."
    new "Thought about drinking myself into a stupor, but I haven't the energy for it."

    old "You know, I started drinking less since we met and you started drinking more. Maybe I'm having a bad influence on you."
    new "You know, I started drinking less since we met and you started drinking more. Maybe I'm having a bad influence on you."

    old "You never had much of a good influence on me."
    new "You never had much of a good influence on me."

    old "Kate had a shocked expression on her face."
    new "Kate had a shocked expression on her face."

    old "How can you say that? I was such a good friend to you growing up!"
    new "How can you say that? I was such a good friend to you growing up!"

    old "Sarah laughed at Kate's theatrics."
    new "Sarah laughed at Kate's theatrics."

    old "Are you kidding me? My dad would constantly scold me for playing with you."
    new "Are you kidding me? My dad would constantly scold me for playing with you."

    old "Each time I came back to the castle, it would be late, and my dress would be a mess."
    new "Each time I came back to the castle, it would be late, and my dress would be a mess."

    old "One time, he almost pulled an entire bird's nest out of my hair."
    new "One time, he almost pulled an entire bird's nest out of my hair."

    old "Ooh yeah, I think we'd gone hunting for sparrow eggs that day."
    new "Ooh yeah, I think we'd gone hunting for sparrow eggs that day."

    old "Only because you told me you had seen a sparrow egg that size of a human head, and I told you I didn't believe you!"
    new "Only because you told me you had seen a sparrow egg that size of a human head, and I told you I didn't believe you!"

    old "Kate suddenly took a strong stance."
    new "Kate suddenly took a strong stance."

    old "Cause I did! I did see it!"
    new "Cause I did! I did see it!"

    old "You're a liar."
    new "You're a liar."

    old "Nah! I swear, an egg as big as a human head."
    new "Nah! I swear, an egg as big as a human head."

    old "Maybe it wasn't no sparrow egg, but I swear I saw it."
    new "Maybe it wasn't no sparrow egg, but I swear I saw it."

    old "Sarah nodded, mockingly."
    new "Sarah nodded, mockingly."

    old "Sure you did."
    new "Sure you did."

    old "You just wanted an excuse for us to run around the woods again."
    new "You just wanted an excuse for us to run around the woods again."

    old "Fine, don't believe me, but I swear I saw an egg that big."
    new "Fine, don't believe me, but I swear I saw an egg that big."

    old "Sarah waved her hand, putting the matter to rest."
    new "Sarah waved her hand, putting the matter to rest."

    old "Sure, one day we'll find an egg that big."
    new "Sure, one day we'll find an egg that big."

    old "And then you're gonna apologize to me."
    new "And then you're gonna apologize to me."

    old "We'll see about that."
    new "We'll see about that."

    old "Kate laughed again."
    new "Kate laughed again."

    old "I didn't miss much of my old life, but I'll say, those days out in the forest with you...I missed those."
    new "I didn't miss much of my old life, but I'll say, those days out in the forest with you...I missed those."

    old "Sarah smiled, for she felt the same."
    new "Sarah smiled, for she felt the same."

    old "I remember I begged my mom and dad for a sister."
    new "I remember I begged my mom and dad for a sister."

    old "I was so small when Thomas was born, but I remember getting really angry that he wasn't a little sister."
    new "I was so small when Thomas was born, but I remember getting really angry that he wasn't a little sister."

    old "But then my mom scolded me, she said that I was now a big sister and that I had to act like it..."
    new "But then my mom scolded me, she said that I was now a big sister and that I had to act like it..."

    old "Sarah smiled at the memory."
    new "Sarah smiled at the memory."

    old "I guess he turned out alright..."
    new "I guess he turned out alright..."

    old "Kate threw her arm around Sarah."
    new "Kate threw her arm around Sarah."

    old "The two were quiet for a while."
    new "The two were quiet for a while."

    old "You're not gonna tell me he's in a better place? Everyone else always tries to tell me some nice story like that."
    new "You're not gonna tell me he's in a better place? Everyone else always tries to tell me some nice story like that."

    old "The rest of em can bullshit you. I'll just be honest."
    new "The rest of em can bullshit you. I'll just be honest."

    old "I don't believe in much of anything like that."
    new "I don't believe in much of anything like that."

    old "I believe...you loved your brother, and you remember him. That's a way he lives on, I guess, through you."
    new "I believe...you loved your brother, and you remember him. That's a way he lives on, I guess, through you."

    old "That's a nice thought."
    new "That's a nice thought."

    old "Kate punched in her shoulder."
    new "Kate punched in her shoulder."

    old "Yeah, surprise surprise, Kate can be a nice person sometimes. I know I come across heartless and all that."
    new "Yeah, surprise surprise, Kate can be a nice person sometimes. I know I come across heartless and all that."

    old "Sarah laughed, shaking her head."
    new "Sarah laughed, shaking her head."

    old "Nah, I know you're actually a softie."
    new "Nah, I know you're actually a softie."

    old "Kate glared at her."
    new "Kate glared at her."

    old "You ever tell that secret to anyone here, I'll beat the shit out of you."
    new "You ever tell that secret to anyone here, I'll beat the shit out of you."

    old "Sarah knew she might actually do it too."
    new "Sarah knew she might actually do it too."

    old "Kate unwrapped her arms and stepped away."
    new "Kate unwrapped her arms and stepped away."

    old "I have to meet up with Ephraim, he wanted to meet up with me for a drink."
    new "I have to meet up with Ephraim, he wanted to meet up with me for a drink."

    old "Is he alright?"
    new "Is he alright?"

    old "Still seems sad, you see it in his face all the time, even when he smiles."
    new "Still seems sad, you see it in his face all the time, even when he smiles."

    old "But you know, I don't think anything other than time will fix him up. Just gotta give him the space and be there for him."
    new "But you know, I don't think anything other than time will fix him up. Just gotta give him the space and be there for him."

    old "Sarah smiled at Kate."
    new "Sarah smiled at Kate."

    old "Softie."
    new "Softie."

    old "Shut the fuck up!"
    new "Shut the fuck up!"

    old "Kate punched Sarah in the shoulder and walked away, laughing."
    new "Kate punched Sarah in the shoulder and walked away, laughing."

    old "I gotta meet up with some of my men, I promised them a few rounds."
    new "I gotta meet up with some of my men, I promised them a few rounds."

    old "Not too many, I hope."
    new "Not too many, I hope."

    old "Kate rolled her eyes."
    new "Kate rolled her eyes."

    old "No mom, I'll promise."
    new "No mom, I'll promise."

    old "Alone again, Sarah continued walking through the camp."
    new "Alone again, Sarah continued walking through the camp."

    old "She passed by Vaelen's tent."
    new "She passed by Vaelen's tent."

    old "For a moment she considered entering, then she thought better of it."
    new "For a moment she considered entering, then she thought better of it."

    old "There wasn't much of anything she'd wanted to talk to him about ever since they had left the road."
    new "There wasn't much of anything she'd wanted to talk to him about ever since they had left the road."

    old "He was the reason for most of this trouble."
    new "He was the reason for most of this trouble."

    old "On only his word, they could have just as easily turned around and returned to Bagrad."
    new "On only his word, they could have just as easily turned around and returned to Bagrad."

    old "They would have been well on their way to Lethram by now. Sitting on a pile of gold, getting fat on good food instead of rationing."
    new "They would have been well on their way to Lethram by now. Sitting on a pile of gold, getting fat on good food instead of rationing."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah heard footsteps behind her. She turned around."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah heard footsteps behind her. She turned around."

    old "Gideon was smiling."
    new "Gideon was smiling."

    old "You thinking about giving him a piece of your mind?"
    new "You thinking about giving him a piece of your mind?"

    old "Is it that obvious?"
    new "Is it that obvious?"

    old "I've been outside his tent a few times too, thinking the same things."
    new "I've been outside his tent a few times too, thinking the same things."

    old "Save yourself the trouble."
    new "Save yourself the trouble."

    old "You're not gonna do it any more than I am."
    new "You're not gonna do it any more than I am."

    old "Gideon waved his arms."
    new "Gideon waved his arms."

    old "Follow me, get a drink."
    new "Follow me, get a drink."

    old "Sarah followed Gideon, ducking in between sleds and campfires until she reached his campsite, a small ways away from the rest of the camp."
    new "Sarah followed Gideon, ducking in between sleds and campfires until she reached his campsite, a small ways away from the rest of the camp."

    old "This is where you sit all by yourself?"
    new "This is where you sit all by yourself?"

    old "Gideon sat down in the glow of the campfire and shrugged."
    new "Gideon sat down in the glow of the campfire and shrugged."

    old "Sometimes."
    new "Sometimes."

    old "I get days where I can't be alone, and then I get days where I can't stand to be around people."
    new "I get days where I can't be alone, and then I get days where I can't stand to be around people."

    old "Sarah looked at the emptiness around the campfire and sat down."
    new "Sarah looked at the emptiness around the campfire and sat down."

    old "Don't you want to be alone now then?"
    new "Don't you want to be alone now then?"

    old "Gideon smiled."
    new "Gideon smiled."

    old "Maybe, but you don't really seem to count in my mind, for some reason."
    new "Maybe, but you don't really seem to count in my mind, for some reason."

    old "Sarah smiled, not sure if this was an insult or a compliment."
    new "Sarah smiled, not sure if this was an insult or a compliment."

    old "So, what's got you troubled?"
    new "So, what's got you troubled?"

    old "Sarah leaned back and casually shrugged."
    new "Sarah leaned back and casually shrugged."

    old "Whose to say I got trouble?"
    new "Whose to say I got trouble?"

    old "Well, first of all, you're walking all about the camp sulking and alone, so that's a pretty good hint."
    new "Well, first of all, you're walking all about the camp sulking and alone, so that's a pretty good hint."

    old "Fair."
    new "Fair."

    old "And second, you're always troubled by something."
    new "And second, you're always troubled by something."

    old "You make me sound morose."
    new "You make me sound morose."

    old "Call it...contemplative."
    new "Call it...contemplative."

    old "That's just a polite way of saying morose."
    new "That's just a polite way of saying morose."

    old "Gideon laughed."
    new "Gideon laughed."

    old "He passed her a cup of beer and Sarah eagerly drank from it, passing the cup back and forth between them."
    new "He passed her a cup of beer and Sarah eagerly drank from it, passing the cup back and forth between them."

    old "You made peace with all this yet?"
    new "You made peace with all this yet?"

    old "Sarah gestured all around them."
    new "Sarah gestured all around them."

    old "This foolish expedition? Nah, still as stupid as the day we got off the road, but..."
    new "This foolish expedition? Nah, still as stupid as the day we got off the road, but..."

